</p>
<p>That's <em>all</em> you need to do to move the cache &amp; logs directories. </p>
<p>In the terminal create a <code>var/</code> directory, and then <code>git mv app/cache/</code> into <code>var/</code>.
Do the same to move <code>app/logs/</code> into <code>var/</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">mkdir var</div><div class="line">git mv app/cache var/</div><div class="line">git mv app/logs var/</div></code></pre>
<p>This might seem weird to you because the cache and logs directories aren't normally
stored in git. But we <em>do</em> keep a <code>.gitkeep</code> file inside each to make sure they don't
get deleted. That's what we just moved.</p>
<p>Back to the browser and refresh! It's still alive! In our IDE, we have a new <code>var/</code>
directory that's happily populated with cache and logs files. </p>
<h2 id="changes-to-bin">Changes to bin/ <a class="headerlink" href="new-dir-structure#changes-to-bin" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Next, look at the <code>bin</code> directory. It exists because <code>composer.json</code> holds a little
bit of configuration: <code>"config:" "bin-dir:"</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="6c9b518ab3">
