</p>
<p>The reason for this is autoloading: you know, the old "your directory structure must
match your namespace" thing. You can sometimes get away with messing this up with
tests... but not always.</p>
<p>This is sweet... except that Composer doesn't know to look in the <code>tests/</code> directory.
Open <code>composer.json</code>. Below <code>autoload</code>, create a new section called <code>autoload-dev</code>.
Below it add a <code>psr-4</code> key for <code>{ "Tests\\": }</code> pointing at the <code>tests/</code> directory:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="e1f05852a2">
