<h2 id="moving-phpunit-xml-dist">Moving phpunit.xml.dist <a class="headerlink" href="new-dir-structure#moving-phpunit-xml-dist" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>On the topic of tests, the <code>phpunit.xml.dist</code> file <em>normally</em> lives in the <code>app/</code>
directory. That's why you run <code>phpunit -c app</code>.</p>
<p>To simplify things, that has been moved to the root of the project:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">mv app/phpunit.xml.dist .</div></code></pre>
<p>After moving it, we need to update a few things. Update <code>bootstrap</code> to <code>app/autoload.php</code>.
In the <code>testsuites</code> section, this is how phpunit know <em>where</em> tests live.
This can now simply be changed to <code>tests</code>... which is pretty cool:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="ffdf6612d1">
